he Ontario Line. Because all six tracks will be on the same level, there will be some opportunity for cross-platform transfers.<!--page 55 of IBC--> East Harbour is also a proposed station for SmartTrack service.<ref name=\"SteveMunro-2017-03-20\" /> In the vicinity of East Harbour Station, there is also a separate proposal to extend streetcar service south along Broadview Avenue into the Portlands.<ref name=\"TheStar-2019-06-24\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2019/04/05/sidewalk-labs-says-it-wont-pay-upfront-costs-for-new-lrt-critical-to-smart-city-waterfront-development.html |title=Sidewalk Labs says it won't pay upfront costs for new LRT critical to 'smart city' waterfront development |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |first=Ben |last=Spurr |date=June 24, 2019 |accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref> The location is the site of the proposed East Harbour office development.\n\n|-\n| Corktown \n| Underground\n| [[Corktown, Toronto|Corktown]]\n| {{rint|toronto|streetcar|504}} [[504 King|King]]\n| Near [[Parliament Street (Toronto)|Parliament Street]] and [[King Street (Toronto)|King Street East]]<ref name=\"TheStar2019-07-22\" />\n\n|-\n| Moss Park<ref name=\"SouthTPAPCompletion\" />\n| Underground\n| {{plainlist |\n*[[Regent Park]] \n* [[Moss Park]]\n}}\n| {{rint|toronto|streetcar|501}} [[501 Queen|Queen]]\n| At [[Sherbourne Street, Toronto|Sherbourne Street]] and Queen Street East\n\n|-\n| {{ttcs|Queen}} \n| Underground\n| [[Downtown Toronto|Downtown]]\n| {{rint|toronto|subway|1}} [[Line 1 Yonge\u2013University|Yonge\u2013University]]<br>{{rint|toronto|streetcar|501}} [[501 Queen|Queen]]\n| Integrated with an existing station at Queen Street and Yonge Street\n\n|-\n| {{ttcs|Osgoode}} \n| Underground\n| [[Downtown Toronto|Downtown]]\n| {{rint|toronto|subway|1}} [[Line 1 Yonge\u2013University|Yonge\u2013University]]<br>{{rint|toronto|streetcar|501}} [[501 Queen|Queen]]\n| Integrated with an existing station at Queen Street West and University Avenue\n\n|-\n| 