auren |last1=Pelley |first2=Mike |last2=Crawley |date=April 10, 2019 |accessdate=April 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410085128/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/doug-ford-toronto-subway-upload-gta-transit-plan-1.5090394 |archive-date=April 10, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"SouthTPAPCompletion\">{{cite web |url=http://reliefline.ca/south/the-project/transit-project-assessment-process/notice-of-completion |title=Notice of Completion \u2013 Notice of Completion of Environmental Project Report Relief Line South, City of Toronto and Metrolinx Transit Project Assessment Process |date=August 14, 2018 |website=Relief Line |publisher=City of Toronto |access-date=August 18, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818214522/http://reliefline.ca/south/the-project/transit-project-assessment-process/notice-of-completion |archive-date=August 18, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"SteveMunro-2017-03-20\">{{cite web |url=https://stevemunro.ca/2017/03/20/how-many-smarttrack-stations-will-survive-ii/ |title=How Many SmartTrack Stations Will Survive? (II) (Updated) |author-link=Steve Munro |first=Steve |last=Munro |date=March 20, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415200846/https://stevemunro.ca/2017/03/20/how-many-smarttrack-stations-will-survive-ii/ |archive-date=April 15, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"sun201904\">{{cite news |url=https://torontosun.com/opinion/columnists/lilley-ford-plan-takes-city-forward |title=Ford's transit plan takes Toronto forward |work=[[Toronto Sun]] |first=Brian |last=Lilley |date=April 11, 2019 |accessdate=April 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412200124/https://torontosun.com/opinion/columnists/lilley-ford-plan-takes-city-forward |archive-date=April 12, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"newsontario\">{{cite news |url=https://news.ontario.ca/opo/en/2019/04/premier-ford-unveils-transportation-vision.html |titl